    <MissileTemplate>
      <AssociatedTemplateName>SGM-H-210 Rapier</AssociatedTemplateName>
      <Designation>SGM-H-210</Designation>
      <Nickname>Rapier</Nickname>
      <Description>$MISSILEGUIDANCE_MODE_CRUISE - $MISSILESEEKER_MODE_ACTIVE_ABBREV(&lt;color=#3BC81E&gt;RADAR&lt;/color&gt;)/$MISSILESEEKER_MODE_ARAD_HOJ_ABBREV(&lt;color=#3BC81E&gt;RADAR&lt;/color&gt;) - $MISSILEWARHEAD_SHORT_HEKP</Description>
      <LongDescription>The &lt;noparse&gt;SGM-H-210 Rapier&lt;/noparse&gt; is a size 2 waypoint-capable cruise missile.  It is based on the SGM-H-2 body, which is a multi-purpose hybrid missile designed to penetrate point defense grids.  This missile will deliver a $MISSILEWARHEAD_DETAIL_HEKP warhead.  It homes in on its target using an Active Radar seeker  If the primary seeker does not find a target or is jammed, it can fall back on a Radar Home-on-Jam seeker.

$MISSILESTAT_CONTROLMETHOD: $MISSILEGUIDANCE_MODE_CRUISE_LONG
